gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 140, Jazz 137
gameRecap.excerpt: Golden State outlasts a late surge by the Jazz to defeat Utah, 140-137. For Golden State, Klay Thompson led the way with 35 points (seven 3PM) and six rebounds, aided by Draymond Green adding 23 points, five rebounds, and five assists, four steals, and two blocks. Collin Sexton led the way with 35 points and nine assists with Keyonte George setting a new career-high in points/3PM tallying 33 points (9 3PM), six assists, and three steals for Utah in the losing effort. Golden State wins and improves to 27-26 on the season, while Utah moves to 26-30 with the loss.
